The paper deals with the problem of continuous speech keyword spotting, which involves filtering out embedded words from a continuous flow of speech. This problem is related to speech recognition and natural language processing, which are sub-fields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
